{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":6635,"text":"¿Hablas español? Parlez-vous français? \n你会说中文吗？"},{"time":12495,"text":"If you answered, \"sí,\" \"oui,\" or \"会\"\nand you're watching this in English,"},{"time":18333,"text":"chances are you belong to the world's\nbilingual and multilingual majority."},{"time":23469,"text":"And besides having \nan easier time traveling"},{"time":25563,"text":"or watching movies without subtitles,"},{"time":27471,"text":"knowing two or more languages\nmeans that your brain"},{"time":29895,"text":"may actually look and work differently\nthan those of your monolingual friends."},{"time":34777,"text":"So what does it really \nmean to know a language?"},{"time":38272,"text":"Language ability is typically measured\nin two active parts, speaking and writing,"},{"time":43133,"text":"and two passive parts, \nlistening and reading."},{"time":46985,"text":"While a balanced bilingual has near equal"},{"time":49655,"text":"abilities across the board \nin two languages,"},{"time":52377,"text":"most bilinguals around the world\nknow and use their languages"},{"time":55760,"text":"in varying proportions."},{"time":57981,"text":"And depending on their situation\nand how they acquired each language,"},{"time":61612,"text":"they can be classified into\nthree general types."},{"time":64915,"text":"For example, let's take Gabriella,"},{"time":67767,"text":"whose family immigrates to the US \nfrom Peru when she's two-years old."},{"time":72007,"text":"As a compound bilingual,"},{"time":73823,"text":"Gabriella develops two linguistic \ncodes simultaneously,"},{"time":78275,"text":"with a single set of concepts,"},{"time":80297,"text":"learning both English and Spanish"},{"time":82165,"text":"as she begins to process \nthe world around her."},{"time":85358,"text":"Her teenage brother, on the other hand,\nmight be a coordinate bilingual,"},{"time":89162,"text":"working with two sets of concepts,"},{"time":91338,"text":"learning English in school,"},{"time":93200,"text":"while continuing to speak Spanish\nat home and with friends."},{"time":96764,"text":"Finally, Gabriella's parents are likely\nto be subordinate bilinguals"},{"time":101845,"text":"who learn a secondary language"},{"time":103410,"text":"by filtering it through\ntheir primary language."},{"time":106198,"text":"Because all types of bilingual people\ncan become fully proficient in a language"},{"time":110215,"text":"regardless of accent or pronunciation,"},{"time":112723,"text":"the difference may not be apparent\nto a casual observer."},{"time":115843,"text":"But recent advances \nin brain imaging technology"},{"time":118619,"text":"have given neurolinguists a glimpse"},{"time":120859,"text":"into how specific aspects of language\nlearning affect the bilingual brain."},{"time":125714,"text":"It's well known that the brain's\nleft hemisphere is more dominant"},{"time":129009,"text":"and analytical in logical processes,"},{"time":131622,"text":"while the right hemisphere is more active\nin emotional and social ones,"},{"time":136202,"text":"though this is a matter of degree,\nnot an absolute split."},{"time":140075,"text":"The fact that language involves\nboth types of functions"},{"time":142883,"text":"while lateralization develops\ngradually with age,"},{"time":145861,"text":"has lead to the critical \nperiod hypothesis."},{"time":148799,"text":"According to this theory,"},{"time":150430,"text":"children learn languages more easily"},{"time":152406,"text":"because the plasticity \nof their developing brains"},{"time":155196,"text":"lets them use both hemispheres\nin language acquisition,"},{"time":158975,"text":"while in most adults, language \nis lateralized to one hemisphere,"},{"time":162992,"text":"usually the left."},{"time":164898,"text":"If this is true, learning a language\nin childhood"},{"time":167684,"text":"may give you a more holistic grasp\nof its social and emotional contexts."},{"time":172480,"text":"Conversely, recent research showed"},{"time":174810,"text":"that people who learned \na second language in adulthood"},{"time":177520,"text":"exhibit less emotional bias\nand a more rational approach"},{"time":181423,"text":"when confronting problems\nin the second language"},{"time":183811,"text":"than in their native one."},{"time":185460,"text":"But regardless of when you acquire\nadditional languages,"},{"time":188109,"text":"being multilingual gives your brain\nsome remarkable advantages."},{"time":192210,"text":"Some of these are even visible,"},{"time":193754,"text":"such as higher density of the grey matter\n"},{"time":196338,"text":"that contains most of your brain's \nneurons and synapses,"},{"time":199441,"text":"and more activity in certain regions\nwhen engaging a second language."},{"time":203504,"text":"The heightened workout a bilingual\nbrain receives throughout its life"},{"time":206889,"text":"can also help delay the onset of diseases,\nlike Alzheimer's and dementia"},{"time":211334,"text":"by as much as five years."},{"time":213225,"text":"The idea of major cognitive \nbenefits to bilingualism"},{"time":215943,"text":"may seem intuitive now,"},{"time":217519,"text":"but it would have surprised \nearlier experts."},{"time":220507,"text":"Before the 1960s, bilingualism\nwas considered a handicap"},{"time":224194,"text":"that slowed a child's development"},{"time":225999,"text":"by forcing them to spend too much energy\ndistinguishing between languages,"},{"time":230652,"text":"a view based largely on flawed studies."},{"time":234089,"text":"And while a more recent study did show"},{"time":236178,"text":"that reaction times and errors increase\nfor some bilingual students"},{"time":239415,"text":"in cross-language tests,"},{"time":241427,"text":"it also showed that the effort\nand attention needed"},{"time":243825,"text":"to switch between languages\ntriggered more activity in,"},{"time":246776,"text":"and potentially strengthened,\nthe dorsolateral prefrontal cortex."},{"time":251465,"text":"This is the part of the brain\nthat plays a large role"},{"time":254142,"text":"in executive function, problem solving,\nswitching between tasks,"},{"time":258971,"text":"and focusing while filtering out\nirrelevant information."},{"time":262644,"text":"So, while bilingualism may not\nnecessarily make you smarter,"},{"time":266480,"text":"it does make your brain more healthy,\ncomplex and actively engaged,"},{"time":270897,"text":"and even if you didn't have \nthe good fortune"},{"time":273422,"text":"of learning a second language as a child,"},{"time":275651,"text":"it's never too late to do \nyourself a favor"},{"time":277794,"text":"and make the linguistic \nleap from, \"Hello,\""},{"time":280572,"text":"to, \"Hola,\" \"Bonjour\" or \"你好’s\""},{"time":283559,"text":"because when it comes to our brains\na little exercise can go a long way."}]}]}